    "title": "Urgent call for payment of due salaries to journalists and media workers before ...",
    "description": "Urgent call for payment of due salaries to journalists and media workers before Eid DHAKA, March 17, 2026: Bangladeshi Journalists in International Media \u2014 BJIM\u2014 is alarmed by the scale of unpaid salaries and delayed wages across national, regional and local media outlets in Bangladesh. As Eid approaches, many journalists, newsroom employees and other media workers remain uncertain about whether they will receive the salaries they have already earned, leaving countless families affiliated with the media and journalism industries under severe financial and emotional stress. Journalists and media staff work under immense pressure, often with little job security, modest pay and growing professional risks. Denying or delaying their due salaries ahead of a major religious festival is not only unjust and exploitative, but also a direct affront to the dignity of media workers and their families. Salaries are not acts of charity from media owners or management; they are a basic professional and legal obligation. BJIM urges all media companies, owners and management bodies to immediately clear all outstanding salaries, festival allowances and other due payments before Eid, so that journalists, staff and their loved ones can celebrate with dignity and without anxiety. We particularly call on outlets with long-standing patterns of wage delays to take urgent corrective action and uphold the minimum responsibilities they owe to the people who sustain their institutions. A healthy media industry cannot be built on the financial suffering of its workers. BJIM stands in solidarity with all journalists and media employees awaiting their rightful pay, and calls on relevant authorities and stakeholders to closely monitor the situation and ensure accountability where workers\u2019 rights are being violated.",
